    "tool_scaffolds": "Generā supportive writing structures matched to your contentum. optiōnēs inclūde: sententia starters (auxilium discipulus begin writing), paragraphus frames (templates with blanks), graphic organizers (vīsuālis structures for planning), and response guides (structured fōrma for specificus textus types). cōnstitūtiōnēs control: scaffold intensity (heavily guided to aperī-ended), contentum specificity (general or topic-focused), and purpose (brainstorming, drafting, revising). Scaffolds reduce writing anxiety and provide entry pūnctum for struggling writers. Gradually reduce scaffolding as discipulus build independence. Exportā as imprimibilis worksheets. cōnsilium: Match scaffold gradus to discipulus need—plūs subsidium initially, fading as peritia develop.",
