    "tool_concept_sort": "Generā sorting certāmen illud develop classification peritia. AI creat: genera (groups for sorting), rēs (things to dispōne), and correct placements. Activity types: simplex dispōne (one genus per rēs), Venn diagramma (overlapping genera), and multi-genus (3+ groups). cōnstitūtiōnēs control: rēs numerā, genus complexitās, and vīsuālis stilus. Sorting builds: critical thinking, comparā-contrast peritia, and conceptual organization. rēs can be: textus, imāgō, or mixtus. Great for: vocābulārium classification, concept differentiation, and aestimātiō. XP praemium for accuracy. cōnsilium: Incipe with simplex binary sorts, advance to Venn diagramma for plūs nuanced thinking.",
    "venn_back_btn": "Exit the Venn diagramma activity and return to the Concept Dispōne configuration pannus. Ūtere when: finished with the activity, want to change cōnstitūtiōnēs, or need to generā novus rēs. prōgressus is servātum; returning to Venn continues where you left off. Back pulsātor is also praestō via keyboard (Escape in some contexts). The configuration pannus allows: regenerating rēs, changing genera, adjusting difficultās, and starting fresh. cōnsilium: Complē and check your current diagramma before returning to capture XP credit.",
    "venn_sorted_item": "An rēs you have already placed in a genus zone. Pulsā to ēlige it and reveal move optiōnēs, or trahe to reposition. While learning, feel free to move rēs between zones as your understanding develops. A checkmark appears on correctly placed rēs after checking. Incorrectly placed rēs can be moved to retry. cōnsilium: place rēs you are confident about prīmus, then ūtere those decisions to inform uncertain placements. Each rēs contributes to your overall accuracy pūnctum. Completely sorted diagramma with high accuracy earn bonus XP.",
    "venn_bank_item": "rēs waiting to be classified. Located in the holding bank below the Venn diagramma. Trahe to the aptus zone: Pōne A (left circulus), Pōne B (right circulus), or Shared (overlapping center). For keyboard users: pulsā to ēlige, then ūtere zone pulsātor to place. Bank rēs repraesentā concepts illud need categorization. All rēs must be placed to complē the activity. rēs can be returned to bank if reconsidering. cōnsilium: Lege the genus labels carefully before placing rēs, and consider what makes rēs similar or different.",
    "venn_move_a": "Place the currently ēlectum rēs into Pōne A (left circulus). Pōne A represents one genus in the comparison. rēs in Pōne A only: belong exclusively to hoc genus, do not commūnicā characteristics with Pōne B. Pulsā when an rēs clearly belongs to just hoc group. Keyboard accessible. After placing, rēs appears in Pōne A zone. Can be moved again if you change your mind. cōnsilium: Place rēs you are most confident about prīmus, then ūtere those decisions to auxilium categorize uncertain rēs.",
    "venn_move_b": "Place the currently ēlectum rēs into Pōne B (right circulus). Pōne B represents the second genus in the comparison. rēs in Pōne B only: belong exclusively to hoc genus, do not commūnicā characteristics with Pōne A. Pulsā when an rēs clearly belongs to just hoc group. Keyboard accessible. After placing, rēs appears in Pōne B zone. Can be moved again if you change your mind. cōnsilium: Think about what distinguishes Pōne B from Pōne A, and place rēs illud fit only Pōne B's criteria.",
    "venn_move_shared": "Place the currently ēlectum rēs in the Shared zone (center overlap). rēs in Shared: belong to BOTH genera, have characteristics of Pōne A AND Pōne B. Hoc is the intersection in the Venn diagramma. Pulsā when an rēs fits both groups criteria. Shared rēs are often the most interesting for discussion because they bridge genera. After placing, rēs appears in center. Can be moved to either single pōne if reconsidering. cōnsilium: Shared rēs are often key concepts illud connect ideas across genera.",
    "venn_move_bank": "Remove the ēlectum rēs from its current zone and return to the holding bank. Ūtere when: reconsidering placement, made an errātum, or want to restart illud rēs. rēs returns to bank ready for re-placement. Does not affect other placed rēs. Useful for: changing your mind, correcting mistakes, and trying different arrangements. Bank rēs can be placed multiple times without penalty. cōnsilium: If unsure about an rēs, return it to bank and focus on rēs you are confident about prīmus.",
    "venn_move_cancel": "Claude the move action index without making changes. The ēlectum rēs stays in its current location. Ūtere when: you accidentally clicked, changed your mind, or want to review before placing. Abrogā does not affect any rēs or your prōgressus. You can ēlige the same or different rēs afterward. Keyboard shortcut: Escape also cancels. cōnsilium: Take your time with placement decisions; there is no penalty for considering carefully.",
