    "header_jump_lesson": "celer navigation back to your most recently creātum or viewed lectiō plan. Saves time when switching between īnstrūmenta and wanting to reference your lectiō. The jump pulsātor remembers your ultimus lectiō plan even across sessiō. If no lectiō plan has been generātum yet, hoc pulsātor aperit the lectiō Plan generator. lectiō plans can also be accessed from the History pannus. cōnsilium: Keep your lectiō plan aperī while generandō supporting materials (glōssārium, quaestiōnārium, scaffolds) to maintain instructional alignment. Multiple lectiō plans are servātum in history for facilis aditus to prior work.",
    "header_bot_toggle": "Mūtā AlloBot visibility on the screen. When hidden: AlloBot does not appear or offer proactive cōnsilium, but remains accessible via colloquium symbolum. When shown: AlloBot floats on screen, provides contextual indicium, and can be interacted with at any time. Cēlā for: distraction-free work, maximum screen space, aestimātiō modus, or discipulus independence. Mōnstrā for: guided exploration, onboarding, troubleshooting, and facultātēs discovery. Different from Sleep modus: Mūtā fully hides the avatar, while Sleep minimizes but keeps it accessible. Bot mūtā state servat with your preferences.",
