    "bot_sleep_btn": "Temporarily cēlā AlloBot from the screen. Ūtere when: AlloBot is distracting during focused work, you want maximum screen space, or discipulus should work independently without AI indicium. AlloBot sleeps but remains accessible—pulsā the bot symbolum in the header or say Wake up to restore. Sleep modus silences all proactive cōnsilium and vōx exitus. AlloBot remembers conversation history when awakened. automaticus wake events: when auxilium modus is activated, when an errātum occurs, or after extended inactivity (checking in). Different from Mute, which silences vōx but keeps AlloBot vīsibilis.",
