    "bot_mute_btn": "Mūtā AlloBot vōx exitus on or off. When muted: AlloBot still displays textus responses but does not loquere aloud. vīsuālis indicator mōnstrat mute status (red līnea through speaker). Ūtere for: quiet classrooms, testing environments, or when sonus is disruptive. Mute affects only AlloBot—other TTS (lege-aloud pulsātor, schedulae memoriālēs sonus) ūtitur separate volūmen controls. AlloBot remains fully functional for typed conversation when muted. Unmute to restore vōx responses. Hoc cōnstitūtiō is independent of the Global Mute pulsātor which silences all sonus application-wide.",
    "bot_mic_btn": "Activate speech-to-textus aditus for talking to AlloBot. Pulsā to incipe speaking—your verbum appear as textus in the colloquium. Requires microphone permission. Benefits: hands-free interaction, faster than typing, natural conversation flow, and accessibility for discipulus with motor difficulties. vōx aditus auto-submits after pause detection or pulsā Mitte. Works alongside typed aditus—ēlige preferred method anytime. Best in quiet environments for accuracy. Noise can cause transcription errātum—loquere clearly and at moderate pace. lingua detection matches your interface lingua cōnstitūtiō.",
    "tool_math": "Creā norma-aligned math problems with scaffolded solutions. facultātēs: vīsuālis representations (numerus līnea, ārea models, graphēma), gradus-by-gradus worked exemplum with magister notes, real-world verbum problems themed to your contentum, differentiated difficultās gradus, and respōnsum keys illud can be hidden for aestimātiō. subsidium conceptual understanding by showing WHY each gradus works, not just HOW. Problems automaticē incorporate vocābulārium from your fōns textus for cross-curricular connections. Exportā as imprimibilis worksheets or interāctīvus digital exercē.",
