    "tool_simplified": "Transform fōns textus into accessible versiō at multiple reading gradus (grades 1-12+). facultātēs inclūde: automaticus Lexile/gradus-gradus adjustment, vocābulārium simplification with hover dēfīnītiō, sententia shortening for struggling readers, and optātīvus bilinguis exitus. subsidium UDL Principle 1 (Multiple Means of Representation) by providing the same contentum at different complexitās gradus. Ūtere Comparā modus to mōnstrā original and simplified side-by-side. Perfect for differentiated īnstrūctiō, ELL scaffolding, and IEP accommodations. AI maintains key concepts while adjusting lingua complexitās.",
    "word_sounds_review_start": "Inīcē the interāctīvus phonics activity ūtendō your prepared verbum list. Before starting, review: verbum are in intended order, phonemes are correctly segmented, imāgō repraesentā concepts well, and activity type is ēlectum. Once started: discipulus work through verbum sequentially (or magister controls pace), each verbum presents the ēlectum activity type (Break It Down, Rhyme Time, or Tracing), prōgressus autosaves, and XP is awarded for mastery. Incipe when your classis is ready—the prīmus verbum appears immediately. You can pause and resume anytime without losing prōgressus.",
