    "word_sounds_review_move_word": "Trahe hoc verbum to a novus position in the activity sequence. Reordering helps: build from simplex to complexus, group thematic verbum together, sequence by phoneme difficultās, or match your lectiō flow. Trahe and dīmitte or ūtere arrow pulsātor for accessibility. Sequence order affects: how discipulus prōgressus through the activity, pacing of difficultās, and narrative flow for fābula-connected verbum. Consider ordering by: syllable numerā (1-syllable prīmus), phoneme type (brevis vowels before longus), or frequency (common verbum before rare). automaticus ordering optiōnēs praestō in cōnstitūtiōnēs. cōnsilium: Preview the full sequence before starting to ensure logical progression.",
    "word_sounds_review_delete_word": "Permanently remove hoc verbum from the current verbum Sounds sessiō. Ūtere when: verbum does not fit lectiō objectives, verbum is inappropriate for discipulus population, or you want a brevior activity. Deletion is immediate and cannot be undone—if you might want the verbum later, consider moving it to the end instead. Minimum verbum numerā is 3 for a valid activity. Deleting below minimum will prompt you to adde plūs verbum before starting. verbum numerā adjusts automaticē after deletion. cōnsilium: Dēlē after reviewing all verbum but before starting the activity with discipulus.",
    "word_sounds_review_play_word": "Preview how hoc verbum will be pronounced during the activity. sonus ūtitur your current vōx cōnstitūtiōnēs (vōx selection, celeritās, volūmen). Audī to: verify pronunciation is correct for your dialect, assess if celeritās is aptus for your discipulus, and exercē your own pronunciation before leading īnstrūctiō. Pulsā multiple times to repeat. sonus is the same as discipulus will hear during activities and on schedulae memoriālēs. If pronunciation seems wrong, check if the verbum has multiple pronunciations (lege vs. lege) and consider adding phonetic indicium in the verbum spelling.",
    "word_sounds_review_play_phonemes": "Hear each individual sound in the verbum spoken separately, then blended. For the verbum CAT: you hear /k/... /æ/... /t/... then cat. Hoc demonstrates phoneme segmentation (breaking verbum into sounds) and blending (combining sounds into verbum)—two foundational peritia for reading. celeritās adjusts automaticē for learner gradus. Builds phonemic awareness, the single strongest predictor of early reading successus. Ūtere for: phonics īnstrūctiō, phonological awareness interventus, and helping struggling readers connect letters to sounds. Research mōnstrat explicit phoneme īnstrūctiō improves decoding peritia.",
    "word_sounds_review_image_gen": "Creā a vīsuālis representation of hoc vocābulārium verbum ūtendō AI imāgō generation. imāgō subsidium vocābulārium acquisition by connecting verbum to concrete vīsuālis (dual coding theory). For abstract verbum, AI creat metaphorical or contextual imāgō. Art stilus follows your current imāgō stilus cōnstitūtiō. imāgō appear in verbum Sounds activities, schedulae memoriālēs, and imprimibilis materials. Regenerate if the imāgō does not clearly repraesentā the concept or you want variety. cōnsilium: Ūtere consistent art stilus within a lectiō for vīsuālis coherence. imāgō can be downloaded for ūtere in other materials.",
    "word_sounds_review_phoneme_bank": "Aditus the complē phoneme library containing all English speech sounds. Ūtere when: a verbum contains a sound not automaticē recognized, you want to adde regional pronunciations, or you are teaching phonemes explicitly. The library inclūdit: consonants (stops, fricatives, affricates), vowels (brevis, longus, r-controlled, diphthongs), and blends. Each phoneme has: IPA symbol, sonus sample, and exemplum verbum. Adde phonemes to your verbum or creā accommodātus phoneme sequences. Essential for explicit phonics īnstrūctiō and accommodating dialect variations.",
    "word_sounds_review_distractor_input": "Accommodā the respōnsum choices for rhyming activities. For Rhyme Time: inscrībe the correct rhyming verbum and distractor optiōnēs illud do not rhyme. Distractors should be: phonetically similar but not true rhymes (creat productive certāmen), age-aptus vocābulārium, and distinct enough to avoid confusion about correct respōnsum. bonus distractors probātiō whether discipulus intellege rhyming patterns versus surface similarity. You can regenerate AI-suggested distractors or creā your own. cōnsilium: Ūtere distractors illud commūnicā consonants but differ in vowels to speciātim target rhyme discrimination peritia.",
