    "persona_reflection_input": "Scrībe a thoughtful reflection after your conversation with the historical/fictional persōna. Prompts guide reflection on: What surprised you? What did you disce? How did hoc change your thinking? Reflections are assessed ūtendō your learning objectives and earn XP based on altitūdō and connection to contentum. Writing develops metacognition (thinking about thinking) and consolidates learning. AI provides feedback on reflection quality. Reflections are servātum to discipulus portfolio and can be shared with magister. cōnsilium: Encourage discipulus to cite specificus moments from the conversation in their reflection.",
    "persona_back_btn": "Go back to the conversation with the historical/fictional persōna. Ūtere when: you want to explōrā plūs topics, need clarification on something the persōna said, or want to probātiō a different līnea of questioning. Your prior conversation is preserved—pick up exactly where you left off. The persōna remembers context from earlier in the conversation. There is no limit to conversation longitūdō, but reflections are due after extended exchanges. cōnsilium: Prepare follow-up quaestiō based on what surprised or interested you in the conversation so far.",
    "persona_submit_btn": "Finalize and submit your written reflection on the persona conversation. Before submitting: ensure reflection addresses the prompt, inclūdit specificus references to the conversation, and mōnstrat thoughtful analysis. After submission: AI evaluates reflection quality, XP is awarded based on altitūdō and insight, feedback appears with suggestions for improvement, and reflection is servātum to your portfolio. You cannot recense after submitting, so review carefully. magister can vidē your reflection and AI feedback. High-quality reflections earn bonus XP and may be featured as exemplars.",
