    "bingo_launch_caller_btn": "Inīcē the interāctīvus Bingo Caller for whole-classis gameplay. Caller displays: current clue (dēfīnītiō lege aloud), vīsuālis of the terminus/imāgō, history of called rēs, and lūdus controls. discipulus audī to dēfīnītiō and find matching terminus on their printed schedula. facultātēs: manuālis advance or auto-lūde modus, adjustable call celeritās, pause/resume, and clear sonus. Perfect for: vocābulārium review, listening comprehension, whole-classis engagement, and kinesthetic learning. magister controls the pace—tardus down for struggling learners, celeritās up for review. The prīmus discipulus to complē a ōrdō/columna calls BINGO!",
    "bingo_exit_caller_btn": "Leave the live Bingo calling interface. Exiting: pauses the current lūdus (resumable), preserves your position in the call list, and returns to the schedula generator. lūdus state is servātum automaticē—reopen Caller to continuā where you left off. Ūtere when: classis period ends, switching activities, or needing to adjust cōnstitūtiōnēs. You can regenerate schedula and return to Caller with novus contentum. Current lūdus statistics (which rēs were called) remain praestō for the sessiō. To incipe completely fresh, regenerate schedula prīmus, then reenter Caller modus.",
    "bingo_speed_slider": "Control how quickly the Bingo Caller advances to the proximus clue during auto-lūde. Range: tardus (20 seconds—gives time to quaere and think), Medium (12 seconds—āctīvus but comfortable), celer (6 seconds—challenging, review pace). celeritās affects: time between clues, reading pace of dēfīnītiō, and overall lūdus duration. For prīmus-time lūsor or complexus vocābulārium, ūtere tardus. For familiar terminus or energetic review, ūtere celer. manuālis modus ignores hoc cōnstitūtiō—you control timing with proximus pulsātor. Adjust mid-lūdus if discipulus need plūs or minus time.",
    "bingo_toggle_history": "Control visibility of previously called rēs. When vīsibilis: discipulus can reference what has been called, catch up if they missed an rēs, and verify their schedula. History mōnstrat rēs in the order called. When hidden: increases certāmen (discipulus must rely on memory), focuses attention on novus calls, and reduces screen clutter. Mūtā anytime during gameplay. History is especially helpful for: auditory processing certāmen, discipulus joining late, and complexus vocābulārium illud needs repeated exposure. cōnsilium: Incipe with history vīsibilis for novus lūsor, cēlā for review rounds with familiar vocābulārium.",
