    "dashboard_clear_all_btn": "Dēlē all discipulus records and restitue analytics to empty. Hoc is permanent and irreversible. All data is removed: discipulus identifiers, activity records, quaestiōnārium pūnctum, and aggregate statistics. Ūtere with extreme caution. Scenarios for clearing: end of semester restitue, testing with demo data, or starting fresh with novus classis. Consider exporting before clearing to preserve records. Confirmation requires explicit acknowledgment. After clearing, dashboard mōnstrat no data until novus discipulus join. Hoc does not affect: your generātum subsidia, servātum lectiō, or magister library. cōnsilium: Clear only when absolutely necessary; archives are usually preferable.",
    "dashboard_close_btn": "Exit the dashboard pannus and return to main workspace. Dashboard data persists—reopening mōnstrat same īnformātiō. Changes made in dashboard (grading, notes) are servātum automaticē before closing. Ūtere claude to: return to contentum creation, reduce vīsuālis complexitās, or focus on other tasks. Dashboard can be reopened anytime from header. If connected to live sessiō, closing dashboard does not end the sessiō—discipulus remain connected. Keyboard shortcut: Escape (in most views). Dashboard automaticē closes when switching to major activities. Your current aspice position is remembered for proximus opening.",
