    "persona_panel": "Engage in AI-powered conversations with historical figures, scientists, authors, or fictional persōna. discipulus ask quaestiō and accipe responses in-persōna based on accurate historical/literary knowledge. facultātēs: Socratic modus (persōna asks probing quaestiō back), reflection prompts after conversation, XP praemium for quality quaestiō, and conversation transcripts for aestimātiō. subsidium perspective-taking, primary fōns analysis, and engagement with contentum. magister can accommodā persōna knowledge and speaking stilus. Great for: history (interview Lincoln), science (talk to Marie Curie), literature (colloquium with Atticus Finch).",
    "persona_card": "Individual persōna schedula for selection. schedula mōnstrat: persōna name, portrait, brevis description, and expertise tags. Pulsā to ēlige for conversation. Multiple selections (2-4): enables pannus discussion modus where persōna interact and debate. Selection optiōnēs inclūde: Historical Figures (scientists, leaders, artists), Literary persōna (from books, plays, myths), Subject Experts (accommodātus personas for domain knowledge), and Custom (creā your own). Selected persōna are highlighted. Deselect by clicking again. pannus discussions creā dynamic multi-perspective conversations great for exploring controversy and multiple viewpoints. cōnsilium: Ēlige persōna with different perspectives for engaging debates.",
    "concept_sort_panel": "Creā categorization activities where discipulus dispōne rēs into groups. Builds conceptual understanding by requiring discipulus to identify attributes and relationships. facultātēs: accommodātus genera (2-4 groups), trahe-and-dīmitte or keyboard-accessible sorting, immediate feedback with explanations, undo/redo for exploration, and analytics showing common misconceptions. subsidium science (living vs. non-living), lingua arts (parts of speech), math (odd vs. even), and any classification task. AI automaticē generat quality distractors. Exportā as imprimibilis cut-and-dispōne or digital interāctīvus.",
