    "persona_free_response": "Type your own aperī-ended response instead of selecting from pre-written optiōnēs. Free response modus promotes creative expressiō, critical thinking, and authentic dialogue peritia. Responses are analyzed for historical accuracy, empathy, and altitūdō of inquiry. Higher-quality quaestiō earn plūs XP.",
    "persona_hints_toggle": "Mōnstrā or cēlā response suggestions and conversation indicium. When enabled, the systēma provides scaffolded quaestiō starters, historical context prompts, and engagement suggestions. Helpful for discipulus novus to historical inquiry or those needing subsidium with aperī-ended questioning. magister can prohibe indicium for plūs prōvectus aestimātiō scenarios.",
    "persona_show_hints": "Display helpful indicium for engaging with the persona. indicium inclūde historically relevant quaestiō to ask, topics the persōna would find interesting, and prompts illud lead to deeper understanding. Great for discipulus who need scaffolding or aren't sure how to begin a historical interview.",
    "persona_submit_btn": "Mitte your nūntius to the persona persōna. Your quaestiō or response is analyzed for relevance and altitūdō. The AI persona will respond authentically based on their historical context, knowledge, and personality. Well-crafted quaestiō illud mōnstrā historical understanding earn bonus XP.",
    "persona_close": "Claude the persona conversation pannus. Your colloquium history and earned XP are automaticē servātum. You can resume hoc conversation later from the History tab.",
    "persona_close_title": "Claude Persona colloquium",
    "persona_reflection_input": "Scrībe your reflection on the conversation for aestimātiō. Reflect on what you learned about the historical figure, how their perspective differs from modern viewpoints, and how hoc conversation changed your understanding. Reflections are evaluated ūtendō a rubric aligned to historical thinking peritia and can earn significant XP.",
    "persona_conclude": "End the conversation and generā a amplissimus summary of your discussion. The summary inclūdit: key topics covered, historical insights gained, quality of your quaestiō, empathy demonstrated, and XP earned. Hoc summary can be exported for aestimātiō, added to discipulus portfolios, or ūsus as a writing prompt for reflection activities.",
    "persona_save_chat": "Servā hoc conversation to review or commūnicā later. Saved chats preserve the complē dialogue, XP earned, timestamps, and any reflections. Ūtere servātum chats for discipulus portfolios, aestimātiō evidence, classis discussions, or exemplar models. Saved conversations can be exported as PDF or shared with other discipulus.",
    "persona_topic_spark": "Get a conversation starter or topic suggestion when you're not sure what to ask. The systēma generat historically relevant quaestiō based on the persona's background, expertise, and time period. Great for overcoming writer's cubus or discovering novus angulus to explōrā in your historical inquiry.",
    "persona_auto_send": "automaticē mitte your nūntius when you dēsiste typing for a few seconds. Creates a plūs natural conversational flow, especially when ūtendō vōx dictation. Prohibe hoc if you prefer to review and recense nūntius before sending, or if you need plūs time to compose thoughtful responses.",
    "analysis_generate_button": "Resolve your fōns textus for reading gradus, complexitās, and facultātēs.",
    "analysis_check_accuracy": "Fact-check the fōns contentum against reliable references.",
    "outline_generate_button": "Generā a vīsuālis organizer from your fōns contentum.",
    "timeline_generate_button": "Generā a timeline of events from your fōns contentum.",
    "timeline_topic": "The main topic or argūmentum of the timeline being generātum. The AI creat historically accurate events based on hoc topic and your fōns contentum. exemplum topics: American Revolution, Life Cycle of Stars, Shakespeare's Career. Events are automaticē ordered chronologically for sequencing exercē.",
    "timeline_count": "numerus of events to inclūde in the timeline. plūs events creā longior, plūs cōpiōsus timelines but increase difficultās. Recommended: 4-6 events for beginners, 8-10 for intermedius, 12+ for prōvectus learners. Events are draggable for sequencing exercē after generation.",
    "faq_custom_instructions": "Adde specificus requirements for the FAQ quaestiō (e.g., 'Focus on misconceptions').",
    "faq_count": "numerus of FAQ quaestiō-respōnsum pairs to generā.",
    "lesson_plan_custom_additions": "Adde specificus activities, norma, or contentum to inclūde in the lectiō plan.",
    "group_modal_container": "classis group manager for organizing discipulus and subsidia.",
    "group_create_input": "Inscrībe a name for the novus discipulus group.",
    "group_create_button": "Creā a novus discipulus group with the entered name.",
    "group_roster_list": "List of discipulus in the ēlectum group.",
    "roster_panel_header": "The classis Roster Key is your differentiation command center. Creā discipulus groups with unique learning profiles (gradus classis, lingua, reading gradus, interests, DOK), then apply those profiles to any generator. Roster data is stored in your browser's local storage and never leaves your device unless you explicitly exportā or sync to a live sessiō. Ūtere 'Apply to Generator' to instantly configure cōnstitūtiōnēs for a group, or 'Differentiate by Group' to batch-generā subsidia for all groups at once.",
    "roster_import_export": "Importā a previously exported roster JSON tabula, or exportā your current roster for backup or sharing between devices. Exported tabula contain group names, color, discipulus assignments, and all profile cōnstitūtiōnēs.",
    "roster_sync_session": "Push your roster group metadata to the āctīvus Firebase sessiō so discipulus are automaticē assigned to their designated group when they join. Group-specificus cōnstitūtiōnēs (TTS celeritās, karaoke modus) take effect on discipulus devices.",
    "roster_batch_generate": "Generā differentiated subsidia for every group simultaneously. Ēlige which subsidia types to creā (adapted textus, glōssārium, quaestiōnārium, etc.) and the systēma will iterate through each group, applying their profile cōnstitūtiōnēs before generandō. subsidia are tagged with group identifiers for facilis filtering.",
    "bridge_send_button": "Aperī Bridge modus to mitte bilinguis nūntius to discipulus during live īnstrūctiō. Type a concept, sententia, or īnstrūctiō, ēlige a modus (Explain, Translate, or vīsuālis+Explain), and ēlige a target group. The nūntius is generātum ūtendō AI with the group's lingua and reading gradus cōnstitūtiōnēs, then displayed as a large, readable bilinguis pannus on discipulus devices with TTS and karaoke highlighting.",
